==Scots==

===Etymology===
From Middle English '''h(o)us''' < Old English '''[[hus|hūs]]''' (dwelling, shelter, house) < Proto-Germanic '''[[*khusan]]''', of unknown origin.

====Pronunciation====
*hUs, /hUs/

===Noun===
'''hoose'''  (''plural:'' '''[[hooses]]''')

# An abode of a human being, a place that a human built to live in; a [[house]].